'''{{nihongo|Iinchō|委員長|}}''' is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] term meaning Chairman.

In Japanese elementary school and junior high school, the class representative (''Gakkyū Iinchō'' or ''Gakkyūiin'') is commonly referred to by the shortened title "iinchō".

In [[anime]], the class iinchō is commonly depicted as a bespectacled girl (''[[meganekko]]'') or boy and is often addressed by their classmates solely by their title rather than by their own name. Examples include:

*Yū Tobita in [[Gakuen Alice]]
*[[Azumanga Daioh minor characters#Masaaki Ooyama|Masaaki Ooyama]] (bespectacled, the first) and [[Chiyo Mihama]] (non-bespectacled, the second) in [[Azumanga Daioh]]
*[[List of characters in Neon Genesis Evangelion#Hikari Horaki|Hikari Horaki]] in [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]]
*[[Characters of Negima (16-31)#Ayaka Yukihiro|Ayaka Yukihiro]] in [[Negima]]
*Eimi Date in [[Pretty Sammy]]
*Ichijo from [[Pani Poni Dash]]
*Shizuka Nagare from [[Doki Doki School Hours]]
*[[Chairperson (Rival Schools)|Chairperson]] from [[Project Justice]]
* Minazuki Yamato in [[Kamikaze Kaitou Jeanne]]

